    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="996"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d996">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.74/7–2352: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 996<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Charge in the United Kingdom (<persName corresp="#p_HJC1"
                            type="from">Holmes</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d996fn1">Repeated to Cairo as telegram 22.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-23T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 23, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>407. In <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>’s continued absence, I saw
                        <persName corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> this morning and, in
                    accordance <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 460 July 22,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d996fn2">In telegram 460, July 22, not printed, the Department of
                        State instructed the Embassy in London to act on Department telegram 437
                            (<ref target="#d993">Document 993</ref>) in view of the fact that
                            <persName corresp="#p_HAN1">Hilali</persName> had just been reappointed
                        Prime Minister. The Department believed that a personal message from either
                            <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> or <persName
                            corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_HAN1"
                            >Hilali</persName> would be most useful and might give him needed
                        support. (745W.00/7–2252)</note> outlined Dept’s suggestions contained
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 437, July 19 re msg from <persName
                        corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> or <persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        >Churchill</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_HAN1">Hilali</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_EMSS1">Mahdi</persName>. I emphasized that if Brit
                    were willing take this action, we for our part wld be willing urge <persName
                        corresp="#p_HAN1">Hilali</persName> accept it in spirit in which it was sent
                    and do our utmost move him away from extreme position. In putting suggestion to
                        <persName corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> I particularly recalled
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>’s statement to <gloss
                        target="#t_Secy1">Secy</gloss> that what Brit want is Sudanese decision on
                    title which wld be as close as possible to what Egypt desires.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> confirmed <persName
                        corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>’s statement represents UK desire. He said
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> wld give careful consideration our
                    suggestion re msg <pb facs="0142" n="1844" xml:id="pg_1844"/> and wld consult
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>. He thought wording would have
                    be looked at carefully as wld question of timing in light reports received from
                    Creswell re army coup in Cairo. I am reporting separately info which <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> gave me re Creswell’s reports on sit in
                    Egypt over last couple days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HJC1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
